olive oil
2 potato
1 packet sesame seeds
½ packet Plant-Based Kumara Patty
1 packet Chilli Jam
1 tsp soy sauce
2 Plant-Based Burger Buns
1 packet slaw mix
1 drizzle rice wine vinegar
1 drizzle sesame oil
1 packet Plant-Based Mayo
2 radish

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut potato into fries. Thinly slice radish.
• Place fries on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and
toss to coat. Sprinkle over sesame seeds, spread out evenly, then bake until
tender, 20-25 minutes.

• When the fries have 10 minutes cook time remaining, heat a large frying pan
over medium heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook plant-based kumara patties (see ingredients) until browned and
heated through, 3-5 minutes each side.
• Remove from heat, then add chilli jam and the soy sauce, turning patties
to coat.

• Meanwhile, bake plant-based burger buns directly on a wire oven rack until
heated through, 3 minutes.
• In a medium bowl combine slaw mix, radish and a drizzle of rice wine
vinegar and sesame oil. Season with salt and pepper.

• Halve burger buns, then spread each bun with a layer of plant-based mayo,
top with radish slaw and a chilli-glazed kumara patty.
• Serve with sesame fries and remaining slaw. Enjoy!